media.description:
I wanted some custom drawer dividers so I made some in Open SCAD and 3D printed them.
They are customizable, and are currently customized to the dimensions of my drawers.
media.title: 20150823 OpenSCAD.png

media.description: This shallow test for fit printed in 16 minutes.
media.title: 20150823_182552.jpg

media.description:
Removed from raft and fits perfect, as expected.
If I want to get really fancy I could add a small roundover to the bottom outer corners, but right now I just want the dividers.
media.title: 20150823_182831.jpg

media.description: This is the taller variation of the divider I needed to fit 6 types of screw, all with the same thread pitch into a single drawer.
media.title: 20150823_190705.jpg

media.description:
Yay!
My screws are organized.

(and I also proved I can print with Fry's PLA with no problem)
